# Vanilla Minecraft Glossaries (dev tool output)

At runtime the engine no longer bundles vanilla glossaries: vanilla terms
arrive via community sync (`sync_community`) as `origin="vanilla"` rows in
the user glossary store, published by the web platform's glossary snapshot.

This directory only holds the output of the dev-side builder used to
generate the web platform's vanilla bundle:

- `tools/build_vanilla_glossary.py` writes
  `vanilla_glossary_{source_locale}_{target_locale}.json` here
  (e.g. `vanilla_glossary_en_us_ko_kr.json`).

Generated files are not shipped in the PyInstaller bundle and must not be
committed.
